
Developed a robust Java application for managing airline reservations, demonstrating proficiency in Java programming and software development principles. Key features include:

Implemented user authentication (sign-up and login) with password encryption for security.
Designed classes to represent Users and Flights, with methods for booking flights, displaying available flights, and managing seat availability.
Integrated functionality for booking multiple seats on flights and displaying booked flights with detailed booking information.
Utilized Java's LocalDateTime for handling flight schedules and Scanner for user input handling.
Demonstrated object-oriented programming principles such as encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism.
